02:33.892 --> 02:35.459
WOW! LOOK AT THAT CRAZY FOOL.

02:35.590 --> 02:37.548
-[WIND HOWLING]

02:37.679 --> 02:39.550
-THAT'S A TRICKY WIND UP THERE.

02:40.508 --> 02:43.337
-[GRUNTING]

02:44.033 --> 02:45.600
-LOOKS LIKE HE'S CAUGHT
IN A THERMAL.

02:50.692 --> 02:55.436
-I MEAN SHE. CALL HEADQUARTERS.
TELL THEM THERE'S A CODE THREE,
TOPANGA CANYON BEACH.

02:57.481 --> 02:59.179
-[GRUNTING]

02:59.309 --> 03:00.441
-WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

03:07.056 --> 03:09.928
-[SIREN WAILS]

04:47.983 --> 04:50.028
-STEPHANIE.

04:50.159 --> 04:52.596
CAPTAIN, I WOULD LIKE YOU
TO MEET OUR LIEUTENANT
STEPHANIE HOLDEN.

04:52.727 --> 04:56.339
-MY DAUGHTER TELLS ME IF IT
WEREN'T FOR YOUR SKILL AND
COURAGE, SHE WOULD HAVE DROWNED.

04:58.036 --> 05:00.169
-THE SKYDIVER.
-OH.

05:00.300 --> 05:03.303
-WORDS CANNOT EXPRESS
THE GRATITUDE I FEEL
IN MY HEART.

05:04.304 --> 05:07.002
SO I WOULD LIKE TO SAY THANK YOU
IN A SPECIAL WAY.

05:07.698 --> 05:09.831
-WHAT KIND OF WAY IS THAT?

05:09.961 --> 05:13.182
-I'M THE CAPTAIN OF
A NORWEGIAN LINE CRUISE
SHIP, THE M.S. SOUTHWARD.

05:13.313 --> 05:17.491
I WOULD BE HONORED IF YOU'D BE
MY GUEST ON OUR NEXT VOYAGE.

05:17.621 --> 05:20.885
-WELL, THAT'S VERY KIND OF YOU,
BUT IT WASN'T JUST ME.

05:21.016 --> 05:23.410
THERE WERE OTHER LIFEGUARDS
INVOLVED IN THE RESCUE
OF YOUR DAUGHTER.

05:23.540 --> 05:26.674
-OH, I KNOW THIS.
I WOULD LIKE TO ASK
THEM ALL TO COME,

05:26.804 --> 05:28.806
EVERYONE WHO PARTICIPATED
IN THE RESCUE.

05:28.937 --> 05:31.287
-WELL, THAT INCLUDES CJ,

05:31.418 --> 05:34.290
SUMMER, MATT, AND, UH...
AND, UH...

05:35.335 --> 05:37.075
WE GOTTA TAKE GUIDO.
HE DID CALL IT IN.

05:37.206 --> 05:38.773
-THANKS, BOSS.

05:38.903 --> 05:40.340
-THIS IS A VERY GENEROUS OFFER,

05:40.470 --> 05:42.037
BUT I'M AFRAID THE COUNTY HAS
STRICT POLICIES

05:42.167 --> 05:44.126
ABOUT LIFEGUARDS
ACCEPTING REWARDS.

05:44.256 --> 05:47.303
-CAPTAIN THORPE
SAID WE COULD GO.
-YES!

05:47.434 --> 05:50.306
-HE SAID IT'S A SLOW SEASON,
AND WE COULD USE THE TIME
TO RECHARGE OUR BATTERIES.

05:50.437 --> 05:52.787
-WHERE ARE WE GOING?
-FOR HOW LONG?

05:52.917 --> 05:54.310
-WHEN DO WE LEAVE?

05:54.441 --> 05:56.225
-IT'S A FIVE-DAY VOYAGE
TO THE MEXICAN RIVIERA.

05:56.356 --> 05:58.053
WE SAIL AT THE WEEK'S END.

05:58.183 --> 06:02.318
-UH, WHAT IF OUR BATTERIES
DON'T NEED RECHARGING?

06:02.449 --> 06:04.755
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
-YOU DON'T WANT TO GO?

06:04.886 --> 06:07.976
-WHAT, ARE YOU CRAZY?
DON'T YOU KNOW HOW MANY
SINGLE GUYS ARE ON A CRUISE?

06:08.106 --> 06:11.849
-IF YOU DON'T WANT TO GO, YOU
DON'T HAVE TO, BUT I WOULDN'T
DISAPPOINT CAPTAIN THORPE.

06:11.980 --> 06:15.026
I MEAN, HE IS LOOKING FORWARD
TO GETTING HIS FEET BACK
IN THE SAND.

06:23.078 --> 06:26.211
-SUMMER, I WANT A NOTE
FROM YOUR MOTHER GIVING
YOU PERMISSION TO GO.

06:26.821 --> 06:29.998
MATT. MATT. YOU, TOO.

06:30.128 --> 06:32.609
-NO PROBLEM. THEY'LL BE
THRILLED TO GET RID OF ME.

06:32.740 --> 06:37.005
-OH, LIEUTENANT HOLDEN,
YOU HAVE MADE MY DREAMS
COME TRUE. [KISSES]

06:37.135 --> 06:40.356
