♪ WE'RE GOING ON A CRUISE,
WE'RE GOING ON A CRUISE ♪

06:40.487 --> 06:43.751
♪ WE'RE GOING ON A CRUISE,
WE'RE GOING ON A CRUISE ♪

06:43.881 --> 06:45.535
♪ WE'RE GOING
ON A CRUISE ♪

06:52.455 --> 06:55.806
-HOW MUCH LONGER?
-WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

06:56.503 --> 06:58.548
LIFE WITHOUT POSSIBILITY
OF PAROLE.

06:59.201 --> 07:00.855
YOU GOT ALL THE TIME
IN THE WORLD.

07:02.378 --> 07:05.250
OF COURSE, AS FAR AS I'M
CONCERNED ALL DRUG DEALERS
SHOULD GET THE DEATH PENALTY,

07:05.381 --> 07:07.427
ESPECIALLY YOU BIG SHOTS.

07:36.717 --> 07:38.762
-UNIT 2, 10-99,
MALIBU CANYON ROAD.

07:50.208 --> 07:52.515
-AMBUSH! SANTA ROSA PEN!
WE'RE UNDER ATTACK!
-KILL HIM!

07:53.473 --> 07:56.258
-IT'S JAMMED!
-KILL HIM!

07:57.389 --> 08:00.784
-LOOK OUT!
-[GRUNTS]

08:10.011 --> 08:11.447
-[ENGINE TURNS OVER]

08:18.019 --> 08:20.587
-WELL, THIS SHOULD BE FUN.
I'VE NEVER BEEN TO MEXICO...

08:23.024 --> 08:24.373
-I'LL GIVE IT RIGHT BACK.

08:36.385 --> 08:39.693
-ALREADY, I'M SMELLING
ROMANCE IN THE AIR.

08:42.043 --> 08:44.654
-DOWN, BOY. DOWN, BOY.
WE'RE NOT EVEN ON BOARD YET.

08:46.830 --> 08:48.353
-YOU'LL BE STAYING IN...

08:49.267 --> 08:53.445
THE ACAPULCO SUITE.
THAT'S MY FAVORITE STATEROOM
ON THE ENTIRE SHIP.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.317
WELL, THANK YOU FOR SAILING
WITH US, MRS. KENILWORTH.

08:55.447 --> 08:57.841
I'LL HAVE BOB OVER HERE
HELP YOU WITH YOUR BAGS.

08:57.972 --> 09:00.888
AND YOU HAVE A BALL.
-THANK YOU, MY DEAR.

09:05.414 --> 09:08.112
-PAMPER HER. HER HUSBAND
JUST DIED AND LEFT HER
A ZILLION DOLLARS.

09:11.115 --> 09:13.291
YOU GUYS MUST BE THE GROUP
FROM BAYWATCH.

09:13.422 --> 09:15.990
THE CAPTAIN SAID WE'D BE HAVING
SOME REAL LIVE HEROES ON BOARD.

09:16.120 --> 09:18.253
OH, I'M AMY BOYER,
YOUR CRUISE DIRECTOR.
-MITCH BUCHANNON.

09:18.383 --> 09:19.994
-HI.
-HI. I'M STEPHANIE HOLDEN.

09:20.124 --> 09:22.605
-NICE TO MEET YOU.
-I'M SUMMER.

09:22.736 --> 09:24.041
-HI. CJ.

09:24.172 --> 09:25.086
-MATT.

09:25.869 --> 09:27.697
-HAVE ANY OF YOU EVER BEEN
ON A CRUISE BEFORE?

09:27.828 --> 09:30.134
-OH, THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
I'VE EVER BEEN AWAY FROM HOME.

09:30.265 --> 09:31.919
-WELL, I'VE SEEN EVERY EPISODE
OF "LOVE BOAT."

09:32.789 --> 09:33.877
-WHAT ABOUT YOU, STEPHANIE?

09:35.313 --> 09:37.838
-JUST ONCE. A LONG TIME AGO.

09:38.752 --> 09:41.319
-WELL, FELLAS, YOUR STATEROOMS
ARE ON THE ATLANTIC DECK,

09:41.450 --> 09:43.321
AND, GALS,
YOU'LL BE ON THE BOAT DECK.

09:43.452 --> 09:45.628
IT'S A LITTLE EASY TO GET LOST,
SO I'LL ESCORT YOU
TO YOUR ROOMS.

09:45.759 --> 09:46.629
COME WITH ME.
-GREAT.

09:48.849 --> 09:49.676
-JUST TAKE IT DOWN.

09:51.112 --> 09:52.635
-GUIDO?

09:52.766 --> 09:55.246
-NO, MAYBE I HAD FIVE.
NO, I KNOW I HAD SIX.

09:55.377 --> 09:56.944
IF YOU COULD JUST LOOK
FOR THE SIXTH BAG.

09:57.074 --> 09:58.859
-GUIDO, COME ON.

09:58.989 --> 10:00.991
-I THINK I'M IN LOVE.

10:02.906 --> 10:05.822
-I HAD FIVE. SIX.
NO, I HAD SIX.

10:12.220 --> 10:13.961
-DID I SEE YOU IN CABO
LAST SUMMER?

10:31.108 --> 10:32.066
-HERE YOU GO.

10:53.130 --> 10:54.044
-HEY!

10:54.175 --> 10:55.742
-ALL: BYE!

11:05.186 --> 11:09.103
-[CHEERING]

11:15.979 --> 11:17.067
-THANK YOU.

11:26.511 --> 11:28.644
-OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR HAVING US.

11:34.432 --> 11:35.520
-OH, THIS IS COOL.

11:47.358 --> 11:50.144
-GUIDO, GUIDO, GUIDO!

11:51.406 --> 11:52.581
YOU KNOW, I MUST ADMIT.

11:53.234 --> 11:55.192
I NEVER PICTURED YOU
AS A LADIES MAN.

11:55.802 --> 11:57.804
-THAT'S ONE OF THE REASONS
I HAD TO LEAVE MY COUNTRY.

11:57.934 --> 12:02.591
OH, SO MANY OF THE WOMEN FOUND
IT VERY HARD TO RESIST MY CHARM.

12:05.942 --> 12:08.989
-HAVING ANY LUCK WITH... UH?
-WITH MRS. KENILWORTH?

12:10.294 --> 12:13.428
IF I PLAY MY CARDS RIGHT,
I'M GOING TO GET THE
START-UP FUNDING

12:13.558 --> 12:17.345
FOR WINDOWS BY GUIDO BEFORE
WE REACH THE FIRST PORT.
[CLICKS TONGUE]

12:17.475 --> 12:20.217
-[CLICKS TONGUE] BE CAREFUL.
-YOU BET.

12:55.862 --> 12:59.648
-I COULD GET USED TO THIS.
-THIS IS SO RELAXING.

13:00.954 --> 13:03.478
-WHEN I LIVED IN FRANCE,
WE CRUISED THE MEDITERRANEAN.

13:03.608 --> 13:06.394
MY DAD WAS WRITING A SCREENPLAY
SET ON THE GREEK ISLANDS.

13:07.917 --> 13:09.789
I GOT MY FIRST KISS
ON THAT TRIP...

13:09.919 --> 13:12.313
DOMINIQUE STENDAHL
FROM MARSEILLES.

13:13.401 --> 13:14.924
I WAS ONLY 12 YEARS OLD,

13:15.664 --> 13:17.666
AND I HAD NO IDEA
WHAT I WAS DOING.

13:17.797 --> 13:20.712
-OH, SOMEHOW, I FIND THAT
VERY HARD TO BELIEVE.

13:20.843 --> 13:23.759
-FORTUNATELY, DOMINIQUE
WAS AN EXCELLENT TEACHER.

13:26.631 --> 13:27.676
WHERE YOU GOING?

13:28.546 --> 13:30.374
-TO GET MY CAMERA.
I LEFT IT IN MY ROOM.

13:32.159 --> 13:35.727
-OH, DON'T LOOK NOW, MR. RIGHT
CAN'T TAKE HIS EYES OFF YOU.

13:54.181 --> 13:55.095
-CHAMPAGNE?

13:57.053 --> 13:59.012
-NO. I DIDN'T ORDER THAT.

13:59.142 --> 14:00.578
-THE GENTLEMAN DID.

14:12.329 --> 14:13.504
-THANK YOU, SIR.

14:13.635 --> 14:14.984
-YOU'RE MORE THAN WELCOME,
MADAME.

14:15.115 --> 14:16.420
-I'M ABIGAIL KENILWORTH.

14:16.551 --> 14:17.944
-YES, I KNOW.

14:19.075 --> 14:22.687
AND I WAS SO SORRY TO HEAR
ABOUT YOUR HUSBAND.

14:22.818 --> 14:25.299
-I'M SORRY. HAVE WE MET BEFORE?

14:25.429 --> 14:27.997
-NOT OFFICIALLY.
ALLOW ME TO INTRODUCE MYSELF.

14:28.128 --> 14:30.739
I'M COUNT GUIDO PAPADOKULOUS.

14:30.870 --> 14:33.742
-COUNT. OH, MY.

14:33.873 --> 14:36.397
I HAD NO IDEA
WE HAD ROYALTY ON BOARD.

14:36.527 --> 14:39.400
-WELL, I LIKE TO TRY
TO KEEP A LOW PROFILE.

14:57.418 --> 14:59.420
-HI.
-HI.

15:08.342 --> 15:09.909
-EXCUSE ME.
-SURE.

15:21.050 --> 15:23.096
-HEY.
-HEY.

15:24.358 --> 15:26.099
-IS IT MY IMAGINATION,

15:26.229 --> 15:28.492
OR ARE YOU JUST COMPLETELY
SOMEPLACE ELSE ON THIS CRUISE?

15:30.277 --> 15:32.409
-IT'S YOUR IMAGINATION.
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

15:33.584 --> 15:35.369
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
WHY ARE YOU SO UPTIGHT?

15:35.499 --> 15:37.849
SD-I'M NOT UPTIGHT. I'M HAVING
A PERFECTLY WONDERFUL TIME.

15:39.112 --> 15:40.113
-STEPHANIE.

15:44.378 --> 15:47.033
-IT'S BILLY.
HE'S RUINING EVERYTHING.

15:48.773 --> 15:50.297
-YOUR EX-HUSBAND, BILLY?

15:50.427 --> 15:52.560
-YES.
-HE'S ON THIS CRUISE?

15:52.690 --> 15:55.302
-NO. I JUST CAN'T STOP
THINKING ABOUT HIM.

15:56.564 --> 15:58.783
WE SPENT OUR HONEYMOON
ON A CRUISE.

15:58.914 --> 16:01.699
SIT'S BEEN A LONG TIME
SINCE I REMEMBERED THE
GOOD TIMES THAT WE HAD.

16:03.527 --> 16:05.051
-YEAH, I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

16:07.488 --> 16:11.318
GAYLE AND I SPENT OUR HONEYMOON
IN HAWAII ON THE BIG ISLAND.

16:12.536 --> 16:15.365
EVERY TIME THERE'S A VOLCANIC
ERUPTION, I THINK OF HER.

16:15.496 --> 16:17.933
[LAUGHING]

16:20.936 --> 16:23.199
-DOESN'T IT MAKE YOU FEEL
SAD OR LONELY,

16:24.461 --> 16:27.464
LIKE YOU WERE A FAILURE
AT THE MOST IMPORTANT
THING IN YOUR LIFE?

16:28.813 --> 16:30.902
-I FELT THAT WAY
FOR A REAL LONG TIME.

16:32.426 --> 16:33.949
THEN, ONE DAY, IT WENT AWAY.

16:34.080 --> 16:37.126
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.
IT JUST WENT AWAY.

16:38.823 --> 16:39.999
-YOU THINK THERE'S HOPE FOR ME?

16:40.129 --> 16:41.391
-ABSOLUTELY NOT.

16:42.479 --> 16:44.699
NOW, COME ON. LET'S GO
HAVE SOME FUN. COME ON.

16:44.829 --> 16:47.136
GO LOSE SOME MONEY AT CRAPS.
COME ON.

16:48.007 --> 16:49.312
-YOU'LL LOSE. I'LL WIN.

